post.summary: Upload a geo collection file to the staging area
post.description: Provides a location for uploading staging files for custom geo collections. Supported file types: GeoParquet (.parquet), GeoJSON (.geojson, .json).

file.description: The geo collection file to upload. Supported formats: GeoParquet (.parquet), GeoJSON (.geojson, .json).

x-gdc-security-info.description: Minimal permission required to use this endpoint.

post.summary: Convert a geo file to GeoParquet format
post.description: Converts a geo file from the staging area to GeoParquet format. Supported source formats: GeoJSON (.geojson, .json). If the source file is already in GeoParquet format, the same location is returned without conversion.

UploadFileResponse.description: Information related to the file uploaded to the staging area.

analyzeRequests.description: List of individual CSV analysis requests.

location.description: Location of the CSV file to analyze.

resultRows.description: Number of rows to return in the flight that represents analysis result. If 0, no rows are returned, if less than 0, all rows that were in the sample are returned.

headerDetectMaxRows.description: Maximum number of rows to work with during header detection.

headerRowCount.description: Number of rows to consider as header, if null, header will be detected.

location.description: Location of the analyzed file in the source data source.

previewData.description: Preview of the first N rows of the file.

items.description: Preview of the first N rows of the file.
Preview of the first N rows of the file.

AnalyzeCsvResponse.description: Describes the results of a CSV analysis of a single file.

name.description: Name of the column as specified in the file (or autogenerated one if the file has no header).

type.description: Type of the column (e.g. string, bool, etc.).

detectedDateFormats.description: List of date formats that can be used to parse this column as date. Null if there are none.

items.description: List of date formats that can be used to parse this column as date. Null if there are none.

AnalyzeCsvResponseConfig.description: Config used to process the CSV file.

checkUtf8.description: Whether to check UTF8 validity of string columns.

columnTypes.description: Information about the column types in the table.

nullValues.description: Sequence of strings that denote nulls in the data.

items.description: Sequence of strings that denote nulls in the data.

trueValues.description: Sequence of strings that denote true Booleans in the data.

items.description: Sequence of strings that denote true Booleans in the data.

falseValues.description: Sequence of strings that denote false Booleans in the data.

items.description: Sequence of strings that denote false Booleans in the data.

decimalPoint.description: The character used as decimal point in floating-point and decimal data.

stringsCanBeNull.description: Whether string / binary columns can have null values.

quotedStringsCanBeNull.description: Whether quoted values can be null.

includeColumns.description: The names of columns to include in the Table. If empty, the Table will include all columns from the CSV file. If not empty, only these columns will be included, in this order.

items.description: The names of columns to include in the Table. If empty, the Table will include all columns from the CSV file. If not empty, only these columns will be included, in this order.

includeMissingColumns.description: If false, columns in includeColumns but not in the CSV file will error out.

autoDictEncode.description: Whether to try to automatically dict-encode string / binary data.

autoDictMaxCardinality.description: The maximum dictionary cardinality for autoDictEncode.

timestampParsers.description: Sequence of strptime()-compatible format strings, tried in order when attempting to infer or convert timestamp values.

items.description: Sequence of strptime()-compatible format strings, tried in order when attempting to infer or convert timestamp values.

CsvConvertOptions.description: Options for converting CSV files when reading.

nullable.description: Whether the data in the given column can be null.

CsvConvertOptionsColumnType.description: Information about a certain column in the table.

delimiter.description: The character delimiting individual cells in the CSV data.

quoteChar.description: The character used optionally for quoting CSV values or false to disable quoting.

doubleQuote.description: Whether two quotes in a quoted CSV value denote a single quote in the data.

escapeChar.description: The character used optionally for escaping special characters or false to disable escaping.

newlinesInValues.description: Whether newline characters are allowed in CSV values.

ignoreEmptyLines.description: Whether empty lines are ignored in CSV input.

useThreads.description: Whether to use multiple threads to accelerate reading.

blockSize.description: How many bytes to process at a time from the input stream.

skipRows.description: The number of rows to skip before the column names (if any) and the CSV data.

skipRowsAfterNames.description: The number of rows to skip after the column names.

columnNames.description: The column names of the target table.

items.description: The column names of the target table.

autoGenerateColumnNames.description: Whether to autogenerate column names if columnNames is empty.

encoding.description: The character encoding of the CSV data.

manifestRequests.description: Files to read the manifests for.

ReadCsvFileManifestsRequest.description: Request to read the manifests of the specified CSV files.

fileName.description: Name of the CSV file to read the manifest for.

version.description: Optional version of the file to read the manifest for. If null or not specified, the latest version is read.

ReadCsvFileManifestsRequestItem.description: Request to read the manifest of a single CSV file.

additionalProperties.description: Map of column names to date formats to use when parsing them as dates.

column_date_formats.description: Map of column names to date formats to use when parsing them as dates.

read_method.description: Method used to read the CSV file.

name.description: Name of the file in the source data source.

version.description: Version of the file in the source data source.

ReadCsvFileManifestsResponse.description: Describes the results of a CSV manifest read of a single file.

size.description: Size of the file in bytes.

modifiedAt.description: Last modification timestamp of the file.

additionalProperties.description: Date formats to use to use to read the given columns.

columnDateFormats.description: Date formats to use to use to read the given columns.

ImportCsvRequestTableSourceConfig.description: Config to use when accessing the data for executions, etc.

name.description: Name of the table the file was imported to.

version.description: Version the file was imported as.

ImportCsvResponse.description: Response containing the information about the imported CSV file.

fileNames.description: Names of the files to delete.

items.description: Names of the files to delete.

ImportGeoCollectionResponse.description: Response after successfully importing a geo collection.

to.description: End timestamp of the removal interval.
